# Conventions

## Commit Messages

Format: `type(scope): description`

```
feat(auth): add OAuth login with Google
fix(session): correct token expiry calculation
test(auth): add OAuth integration tests
docs(api): update authentication endpoints
refactor(auth): extract OAuthProvider interface
chore: update dependencies
perf(db): add index on user.email
ci: add security audit step
```

**Types:** `feat` | `fix` | `refactor` | `test` | `docs` | `chore` | `perf` | `ci`

Rules:
- Imperative mood: "add" not "added" or "adds"
- Lowercase, no trailing period
- Max 72 chars on first line
- Scope is the affected module/component

## Branch Names

```
feature/feat-001-oauth-login
fix/bug-042-session-expiry
chore/update-dependencies
```

## Spec IDs

- Features: `FEAT-001`, `FEAT-002`, ...
- Bugs: `BUG-001`, `BUG-002`, ...

Zero-padded to 3 digits. Never reuse an ID.

## Version Tags

Format: `v{MAJOR}.{MINOR}.{PATCH}` — e.g., `v1.2.3`

Follows [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/):
- PATCH: bug fixes only
- MINOR: new features, backwards-compatible
- MAJOR: breaking changes

## File Structure Conventions

- One module per file; keep files under ~300 lines
- `src/` — all production source code
- `tests/` — all test files, mirroring `src/` structure
- `docs/` — documentation (never generated, always human/AI readable)
- `.claude/` — AI workflow infrastructure (don't hand-edit)
